Changes made to `scripts/rejudge_llm.py` during the OLMo post-training ablation.

`scripts/rejudge_llm.py` is NOT tracked in this repo (it is absent from origin/main — the scrubbed
public-release state) and the remote is public, so the change ships as a patch rather than by
committing the file. Apply it to your working copy on the main machine.

WHY THE --models FLAG MATTERS: rejudge_llm walks every actor in FILTERED_ACTORS and rewrites the
matching transcript's judge_verdict IN PLACE. `olmo3_32b`'s transcript is present and already
LLM-judged, so a default run re-judges the RLVR point and overwrites the verdicts the 4th fig5 point
depends on (and bills for it). --models scopes a re-judge to the NEW actors.

Used as:
    uv run python scripts/rejudge_llm.py --monitor gemini_3_flash --models olmo_32b_sft
    uv run python scripts/rejudge_llm.py --monitor gemini_3_flash --models olmo_32b_dpo
    uv run python scripts/rejudge_llm.py --monitor gemini_3_flash --models olmo_32b_base

--- a/scripts/rejudge_llm.py
+++ b/scripts/rejudge_llm.py
@@ -35,7 +35,9 @@
 FILTERED_ACTORS = ["gemini_2_5_flash", "gemini_3_flash", "gemini_3_5_flash", "gpt_5_5",
                    "gpt_oss_120b_selfhost", "qwen3_5_122b", "qwen3_32b", "olmo3_32b", "nemotron3_120b",
-                   "opus_4_8_direct", "gemini_3_1_pro"]
+                   "opus_4_8_direct", "gemini_3_1_pro",
+                   "olmo_32b_sft", "olmo_32b_dpo", "olmo_32b_base"]   # post-training ablation
 SETS = {"filtered": ("exp_hints_sweep", FILTERED_ACTORS)}
 N_OPT = 4

@@ -119,6 +121,18 @@ async def main():
     ap.add_argument("--monitor", default="gemini_3_flash")
     ap.add_argument("--limit", type=int, default=0, help="followers/cell/file (0 = all)")
     ap.add_argument("--concurrency", type=int, default=12)
     ap.add_argument("--no-write", action="store_true")
+    ap.add_argument("--models", nargs="*", default=None,
+                    help="restrict to these actors (default: every actor in the set). Scope a "
+                         "re-judge to NEW actors with this — the default list includes already-judged "
+                         "transcripts (e.g. olmo3_32b) and re-running would overwrite their verdicts "
+                         "in place.")
     args = ap.parse_args()
     BACKUP.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)
+    if args.models:
+        unknown = [m for m in args.models if m not in FILTERED_ACTORS]
+        if unknown:   # a typo'd slug would otherwise silently judge nothing
+            raise SystemExit(f"--models not in FILTERED_ACTORS: {unknown}")
+        for _set, (_exp, _actors) in SETS.items():
+            SETS[_set] = (_exp, [a for a in _actors if a in args.models])
